# =============================================================================
# Trivy Ignore List — Accepted CVE Risks
# https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore
#
# These CVEs are from transitive dependencies of upstream applications
# and cannot be fixed without breaking compatibility. They are reviewed
# monthly and removed once upstream updates.
#
# The nightly security-scan.yml workflow runs Grype independently of this
# file and reports HIGH/CRITICAL published-image findings with fixes available.
#
# Last reviewed: 2026-04-25
#
# Remediated (2026-04-03):
#   - gosu 1.14→1.19: All 30+ Go stdlib CVEs eliminated (5 Debian images)
#   - npm/yarn/corepack stripped from runtime: ~15 HIGH CVEs eliminated (dashy)
#   - Caddy v2.9.1→v2.11.2: 11 CVEs eliminated (caddy deps + Go stdlib)
#   - Syncthing v1.29.2→v2.0.15: Go runtime upgrade + SHA256 verification
#   - WireGuard UI Go 1.22→1.26 + x/crypto upgraded: 9 CVEs eliminated
# =============================================================================

# --- Sonarr / Radarr .NET transitive dependencies ---

# System.Text.Json 6.0.9 → fix in 6.0.10/8.0.5 (bundled by Sonarr upstream)
# DoS in JSON parser — low risk, only processes internal API payloads
CVE-2024-43485

# MimeKit (bundled by Sonarr/Radarr upstream)
# CRLF Injection in Quoted Local-Part — low risk, images do not send email
CVE-2026-30227

# Microsoft.Bcl.Memory (bundled by Sonarr upstream via .NET runtime)
# DoS via memory allocation — low risk, internal API payloads only
CVE-2026-26127

# Microsoft.AspNetCore (bundled by Sonarr upstream via .NET runtime)
# DoS vulnerability — low risk, not internet-facing without reverse proxy
CVE-2026-26130

# Microsoft.IdentityModel.JsonWebTokens 6.8.0 → fix in 6.34.0 (bundled by Sonarr upstream)
# .NET Identity DoS — medium risk, internal API only, no external JWT validation
CVE-2024-21319

# System.Net.Http 4.3.0 → fix in 4.3.4 (bundled by Sonarr upstream)
# Redirect credential disclosure — low risk, these apps do not follow attacker-
# controlled auth redirects in normal container use
CVE-2018-8292

# System.Private.Uri 4.3.0 → fix in 4.3.2 (bundled by Sonarr/Radarr upstream)
# Uri/IP parsing DoS — low risk, these apps process trusted local API traffic
# and are typically reverse-proxied rather than internet-exposed directly
CVE-2019-0980
CVE-2019-0981

# System.Text.RegularExpressions 4.3.0 → fix in 4.3.1 (bundled by Sonarr upstream)
# Regex timeout bypass DoS — low risk, no untrusted regex execution surface is
# exposed by normal container operation
CVE-2019-0820

# --- SABnzbd Python transitive dependencies --- REMOVED
# SABnzbd has been replaced by Transmission (compiled C++ binary, no Python deps)

# --- Dashy Node.js transitive dependencies ---
# These are upstream Dashy application dependencies pinned by yarn.lock.
# Fixes require MAJOR version bumps (glob 10→11, minimatch 9→10, tar 6→7)
# that would break the application build. Dashy runs behind a reverse proxy
# in a trusted home network; these deps process only local dashboard config.
# Review: 2026-05-01

# cross-spawn 7.0.3 → fix in 7.0.5 (Dashy transitive dep)
# ReDoS via malicious command arguments — low risk, no user-supplied command execution
CVE-2024-21538

# glob 10.4.2 → fix in 11.1.0 (Dashy transitive dep, MAJOR bump required)
# Command injection via malicious patterns — low risk, only processes local config
CVE-2025-64756

# lodash 4.17.23 → fix in 4.18.0 (Dashy transitive dep)
# Incomplete prototype pollution fix — low risk, dashboard processes trusted config only
CVE-2026-4800

# minimatch 9.0.5 → fix in 10.2.1+ (Dashy transitive dep, MAJOR bump required)
# ReDoS via crafted patterns — low risk, patterns come from local config only
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# tar 6.2.1 → fix in 7.5.3+ (Dashy transitive dep, MAJOR bump required)
# Arbitrary file overwrite/creation/read via path traversal — low risk, Dashy
# does not extract user-supplied archives; tar is a build-time transitive dep
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802

# lodash 4.17.23 — Prototype Pollution via array path bypass in _.unset/_.omit
# Requires attacker-controlled property paths — low risk, Dashy processes trusted
# local dashboard config only; no untrusted input reaches lodash path functions
# Review: 2026-05-01
CVE-2026-2950

# nuxt (via vue-js-modal/examples/) — XSS in navigateTo after SSR
# Found in example code of a transitive dep, not used at Dashy runtime
# Review: 2026-05-01
CVE-2024-34343

# brace-expansion (via npm internal deps, not Dashy application code)
# DoS via zero step value + ReDoS — low risk, npm is not invoked at runtime;
# patterns come from trusted local config only
# Review: 2026-05-01
CVE-2026-33750
CVE-2025-5889

# vue 2.x — ReDoS in template compiler
# Low severity, Dashy compiles templates at build time only, not at runtime
# from untrusted input
# Review: 2026-05-01
CVE-2024-9506

# jsdiff (via npm internal deps, not Dashy application code)
# DoS in parsePatch/applyPatch — low risk, npm diff not invoked at runtime
# Review: 2026-05-01
CVE-2026-24001

# --- gosu 1.19 Go stdlib CVEs (affects sonarr, radarr, prowlarr, plex, transmission) ---
# gosu 1.19 is the latest release, compiled with Go 1.24.6. No newer version exists.
# gosu is a minimal setuid/setgid tool (~1.8MB static binary) that ONLY calls
# setuid(2)/setgid(2) and exec(2). It never uses crypto/tls, archive/tar,
# archive/zip, net/url, or crypto/x509 — these are UNREACHABLE code paths
# embedded in the Go stdlib by the compiler. Zero exploitation risk.
# Review: 2026-05-01

# crypto/tls — session resumption DoS (fixed in Go 1.24.13)
# gosu does not make or accept TLS connections
CVE-2025-68121

# archive/tar — unbounded allocation (fixed in Go 1.24.8)
# gosu never opens tar archives
CVE-2025-58183

# net/url — memory exhaustion via crafted URLs (fixed in Go 1.24.12)
# gosu never parses URLs
CVE-2025-61726

# archive/zip — excessive CPU via crafted zip (fixed in Go 1.24.12)
# gosu never opens zip archives
CVE-2025-61728

# crypto/x509 — DoS in certificate parsing (fixed in Go 1.24.11)
# gosu never parses X.509 certificates
CVE-2025-61729

# net/url — IPv6 zone ID parsing issue (fixed in Go 1.25.8)
# gosu never parses URLs
CVE-2026-25679

# database/sql — race condition in connection pool (fixed in Go 1.23.12)
# gosu never uses database/sql
CVE-2025-47907

# os — FileInfo can escape from a Root (fixed in Go 1.25.8, 1.26.1)
# gosu never uses os.Root filesystem sandboxing
CVE-2026-27139

# html/template — URL escaping in meta content attributes (fixed in Go 1.25.8, 1.26.1)
# gosu never renders HTML templates
CVE-2026-27142

# crypto/tls — TLS 1.3 handshake multiple messages DoS (fixed in Go 1.24.12)
# gosu never makes or accepts TLS connections
CVE-2025-61730

# crypto/x509 — wildcard SAN constraint bypass (fixed in Go 1.24.12)
# gosu never validates X.509 certificates
CVE-2025-61727

# net/mail — excessive CPU in ParseAddress (fixed in Go 1.24.12)
# gosu never parses email addresses
CVE-2025-61725

# net/textproto — excessive CPU in ReadResponse (fixed in Go 1.24.12)
# gosu never reads textproto responses
CVE-2025-61724

# encoding/pem — quadratic complexity on invalid input (fixed in Go 1.24.12)
# gosu never parses PEM data
CVE-2025-61723

# crypto/tls — ALPN negotiation error leaks attacker data (fixed in Go 1.24.8)
# gosu never makes or accepts TLS connections
CVE-2025-58189

# crypto/x509 — panic on DSA public keys (fixed in Go 1.24.8)
# gosu never parses X.509 certificates
CVE-2025-58188

# crypto/x509 — quadratic complexity in name constraints (fixed in Go 1.24.8)
# gosu never parses X.509 certificates
CVE-2025-58187

# net/http — cookie parsing memory exhaustion (fixed in Go 1.24.8)
# gosu never handles HTTP requests
CVE-2025-58186

# encoding/asn1 — DER parsing memory exhaustion (fixed in Go 1.24.8)
# gosu never parses ASN.1/DER data
CVE-2025-58185

# net/url — insufficient IPv6 hostname validation (fixed in Go 1.25.0)
# gosu never parses URLs
CVE-2025-47912

# --- Caddy v2.11.2 transitive dependency CVEs ---
# Caddy v2.11.2 pulls smallstep/certificates v0.30.0-rc3 (the RC of the
# fix version v0.30.0). The final release patches these CVEs but Caddy
# hasn't updated its go.mod yet. These affect the Step CA ACME provisioner;
# our Caddy image is used as a reverse proxy in a home network, not as a
# public certificate authority. Zero exploitation risk in this context.
# Review: 2026-05-01

# smallstep/certificates — unauthenticated ACME provisioner access
CVE-2026-30836

# smallstep/certificates — ACME provisioner privilege escalation
CVE-2025-44005

# go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.40.0 → fix in v1.43.0 (Caddy transitive dep)
# BSD-only PATH hijack via the kenv command; this repository builds Linux
# containers, so the affected BSD-specific code path is unreachable
CVE-2026-39883

# --- WireGuard UI v0.6.2 Go dependency CVEs ---
# WireGuard UI v0.6.2 (last release Oct 2023) pins golang.org/x/crypto
# v0.17.0. Updating causes cascading dependency breakage (wireguard
# module API changes). These CVEs affect the x/crypto/ssh package;
# WireGuard UI is a web application that never uses SSH functionality.
# Review: 2026-05-01

# golang.org/x/crypto/ssh — PublicKeyCallback misuse
# Only affects code using SSH server/client auth; WireGuard UI is HTTP-only
CVE-2024-45337

# golang.org/x/crypto/ssh — DoS via SSH banner
# Same: WireGuard UI never handles SSH connections
CVE-2025-22869

# golang.org/x/net/html — input neutralization (XSS)
# WireGuard UI does not use x/net/html for untrusted content rendering
CVE-2025-22872

# golang.org/x/net/proxy — HTTP proxy bypass via IPv6 zone ID
# WireGuard UI does not proxy HTTP requests through x/net/proxy
CVE-2025-22870

# net/http — CONTINUATION frame DoS (affects Go <1.22.9)
# WireGuard UI runs behind a reverse proxy; internal HTTP not internet-exposed
CVE-2023-45288

# golang.org/x/crypto/ssh — GSSAPI authentication DoS via unbounded memory
# WireGuard UI never uses SSH/GSSAPI authentication
CVE-2025-58181

# golang.org/x/crypto/ssh/agent — DoS via malformed messages
# WireGuard UI never acts as an SSH agent
CVE-2025-47914

# --- Caddy v2.11.2 transitive dependency CVE ---
# Caddy v2.11.2 pins google.golang.org/grpc v1.79.1; fix requires v1.79.3.
# gRPC is used internally by Caddy plugins — the admin API listens on
# localhost:2019 only. In a reverse proxy context behind a firewall,
# the gRPC attack surface is not externally reachable.
# Review: 2026-05-01
CVE-2026-33186

# go-jose/go-jose/v3 v3.0.4 → fix in v3.0.5 (Caddy transitive dep)
# Panic in JWE decryption — low risk, Caddy does not process external JWE
# tokens. Used internally by ACME/step-ca integration. Home network context.
# Review: 2026-05-01
CVE-2026-34986
